WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:15.240
Passing the eval is only half the story. This section asks
the question that actually pays your bills. Across the
whole lifecycle of evals, funding, and payouts, what do
you net versus what you spend?

2
00:00:15.840 --> 00:00:30.264
This is Best ROI to Flip. It models the full prop
lifecycle. Buying evals, passing them, getting funded, and
pulling payouts. Then it nets all of that against the cash
you burned on accounts and resets. Three winners, just
like the last section.

3
00:00:30.864 --> 00:00:43.584
Best ROI per dollar spent is the headline. The most net
profit for every single dollar of eval and reset spend.
When you see a number like eighteen thousand percent,
that's net dollars earned for each dollar you burned
getting there.

4
00:00:44.184 --> 00:00:55.008
Fastest Payout is speed against the account price. The
move that reaches your first real withdrawal soonest. If
cash flow in your pocket matters more than total profit on
paper, this is your move.

5
00:00:55.608 --> 00:01:06.144
And Cheapest to Profit is the lowest total spend to simply
turn net-positive. The least money at risk before the
whole operation pays for itself. It's the conservative,
capital-light way in.

6
00:01:06.744 --> 00:01:19.728
So ROI rewards efficiency, payout rewards speed, and
cheapest rewards safety. If you're funding this from a
small bankroll, start with Cheapest or Best ROI. If you've
got capital sitting idle, chase the payout instead.

7
00:01:20.328 --> 00:01:25.656
Passing is a milestone. Getting paid is the point. This is
the section that measures the point.
